  "post_multiplication_note": "DP-3 \u03b3 post-multiplication is a SCALAR ADJUSTMENT applied to OOT posterior-predictive output AFTER the fit; it is NOT a Bayesian fit, NOT a regression coefficient, and NOT a control variable. Justified because we have direct external evidence (training OLS slope on per-week LTV-per-conv) that LTV-per-conv is drifting upward, and the model's specification implicitly assumes it is fixed. Adjusted predictions, HDI bounds, and metrics are the canonical outputs for downstream comparison; raw outputs are preserved in the *_raw fields for transparency.",
  "notes": "M2 uses D-\u03b5 (per-window lift priors + post-multiply OOT). NO trend regressor \u2014 handles the LTV-per-conv drift asymmetrically from M1's conversion-volume drift. See post_multiplication_note for DP-3 \u03b3 caveat."
